rows.title: Intro
rows.titleText: As you're walking back home to your apartment after a long day of work, the world has fallen into its nightly silence, the air unnaturally still and heavy. The distant streetlights cast eerie shadows along the sidewalks and buildings, while the hooting of owls seems to grow louder as the night deepens. Out of the corner of your eye, you catch a glimpse of a strange face peering at you from the darkness, its features indistinct but its intent known, It speaks in s voice low and guttural, a rasping whisper that seems to come from all around you. "Why hello there, Wo- Human" "You seem...rather in need of a deal, don't you agree? Shall we make a bargain?"

objects.text: <b>Scream every ounce of air out of your lungs.<b>

rows.title: The Outcome
rows.titleText:
So, What decision you end up making in your panic?
And how did it turn out for you?

objects.title: I Froze
objects.text: You stand frozen in terror, unable to move or speak as the creature looms over you. It seems confused at your lack of response, but soon comes to a realization. "You alright there? Is this what you creatures call freezing up? I don't know how to go on from here.. I will just leave."

objects.title: I Choose Violence
objects.text: Your panic drives you to lash out, your fist landing a punch on the face of the shadowy figure. To your surprise, you hear it recoil in pain. "Fine, mortal. You want to reject my deals? Then you can have it your way, I will just pursue someone who is."

rows.title: Intro
rows.titleText: A sudden burst of blinding light illuminates the surroundings, accompanied by a soothing, gentle voice that immediately calms your nerves after the preceding harrowing encounter. You catch sight of a shadowy figure, its silhouette remarkably similar to the entity you encountered earlier yet carrying a gentler, more compassionate aura. "I'm in absolute disbelief that you nearly consented to that... Him?" She expresses with concern, her voice filled with a motherlike tenderness. "You poor, poor soul... I can see how he toyed with you, how he made you dance to his whims... He tends to make a mess, And I have to clean it all up. Oh my, I haven't introduced myself did I?" Her tone is pleasant, but there’s something beneath it—something too perfect about her words, too scripted.

objects.text: "Greetings. I’m sure you’ve met my brother before. He goes by the name ‘Benefactor,’ though I must admit, I don’t quite understand the reasoning behind that title." She pauses, letting out a soft sigh, then leans in slightly, her eyes now sharp with focus. “You... are very fortunate, you know. Lucky to encounter him and not fall victim to one of his deals. My brother, you see, is a cruel being. He forces people into choices, promising them power, and then stripping away their existence as payment—taking everything for something they never truly wanted—all because he finds human suffering amusing" Her smile is calm, but there's something distant in her voice, almost like she’s speaking of something else entirely. “I’ve had to clean up after him more times than I care to admit. Ensuring nothing too significant happens, that nothing brings harm to others. Sometimes I wonder... why are brothers always such a nuisance?” “As I was saying, my brother thrives on chaos— He loves watching the world burn. But I’m not like him. I don’t care for senseless drama. What I care about is order A world where every soul knows their place, where power isn’t wasted in games, but used to benefit everyone.” Her voice grows more measured, almost reassuring, as if she’s presenting an offer too good to refuse. “You see, my dear, I don’t need the world to burn. I need it to heal. I need it to be perfect. And I need your help to make sure it stays that way.”

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
